.TH TOS 1 "2026-06-01" "0.1.0" "Translation of Service"
.SH NAME
tos \- peer\-to\-peer typed data sync
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tos
[\fIglobal options\fR]
\fIcommand
[\fIcommand options\fR]
[\fIarguments\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
ToS moves rows between any source and any destination (PostgreSQL,
MySQL, SQLite, MongoDB, Redis, JSON, YAML, TXT, JSONL) using a typed
schema description language. It can run as a one-shot CLI, a fan-out
sync, or a long-running daemon driven by a TOML topology.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B push \-\-from <URI> \-\-to <URI> [\-\-table <NAME>]
Read from the source URI and write every row to the destination URI.
.TP
.B sync \-\-from <URI> \-\-to <URI> [\fI--to <URI>\fR...] [\-\-watch]
Like
.BR push ,
but writes to multiple destinations concurrently, continuing on
per-destination errors.
.TP
.B schema pull|push|infer|diff|validate
Inspect, propagate, derive, compare, or validate ToS SDL schemas.
.TP
.B topology show|validate
Show or validate a TOML topology file.
.TP
.B node start|stop|status|id
Run the daemon. \fBstart\fR reads \fI/etc/tos/topology.toml\fR (or
\fB--config\fR), launches every pipeline in its own task, and blocks on
\fBSIGINT\fR/\fBSIGTERM\fR.
.TP
.B status [\fI--config\fR]
Show the loaded topology summary.
.TP
.B log [\fI--lines N\fR]
Tail the tracing log.
.TP
.B help
Print command-specific help.
.SH URI SCHEMES
.TP
.B mock://<table>?records=N
In-process synthetic source.
.TP
.B postgres://USER:PASS@HOST/DB?table=NAME[&schema=SCHEMA]
Read or write a PostgreSQL table.
.TP
.B mysql://USER:PASS@HOST/DB?table=NAME
Read or write a MySQL/MariaDB table.
.TP
.B sqlite:///path/to.db?table=NAME
Read or write a SQLite file.
.TP
.B mongodb://HOST/DB?table=NAME
Read or write a MongoDB collection.
.TP
.B redis://HOST:PORT?prefix=KEY_PREFIX
Read or write Redis hashes, one hash per key.
.TP
.B json:///path/to.json
Read or write a JSON file (array of objects).
.TP
.B jsonl:///path/to.jsonl
Read or write a JSON Lines file (one object per line).
.TP
.B yaml:///path/to.yaml
Read or write a YAML sequence of mappings.
.TP
.B txt:///path/to.txt?delimiter=|
Read or write a delimited text file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS One-shot PostgreSQL → JSON
.PP
.nf
tos push \\
    \-\-from postgres://app:secret@db.local/app?table=users \\
    \-\-to   json:///var/backup/users.json
.fi
.SS Fan-out with watch
.PP
.nf
tos sync \\
    \-\-from postgres://app:secret@db.local/app?table=orders \\
    \-\-to   sqlite:///var/cache/orders.db?table=orders \\
    \-\-to   redis://cache.local:6379?prefix=tos:orders \\
    \-\-watch
.fi
.SS Run the daemon
.PP
.nf
sudo systemctl start tos.service
journalctl \-u tos \-f
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/tos/topology.toml
Default daemon topology.
.TP
.I /usr/local/share/man/man1/tos.1
This manual page.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success, 1 on protocol or schema error, 2 on usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cargo (1),
.BR sqlite3 (1),
.BR psql (1)
.PP
